@N0216:  total length of line in pixels
@N0220:  draw a point at the end of the line
@N0223:  initialize point gen with the y-coord in ACC
@N0227:  Draw a point with ACC = x
@N0230:  placeholder
@N0233:  constants
@N0243:  loop counter for 12 iterations
@N0254:  +32 in the top half of the word
@N0255:  +32 in the bottom half of the word
@N0262:  ephemeral args used for passing parameters
@N0264:  loop counter
@N0266:  save the return address
@N0270:  initialize vector gen; Y offset in ACC
@N0272:  shift from 0-15 axis to -8 to +7
@N0274:  re-fetch the next x_arg
@N0275:  multiply by 128 to get +/- 1024 screen coords, multiply by 64 to get to bit 0
@N0276:  Draw a segment with x=ACC
@N0300:  increment the segment counter
@N0303:  save the return address
@N0310:  initialize vector gen with the y-coord in ACC
@N0312:  shift from 0-15 axis to -8 to +7
@N0313:   +/- 1024 screen coords, multiply by 64 to get to bit 0
@N0314:  Draw a segment with x=ACC, length=32 in vert_line_seg
@N0317:  move up one segment
@N0322:  shorten the remaining length by 32
@N0324:  test to see if y_len remaining is less than 32
@N0326:  otherwise, go round again for the next segment
@N0327:  pick up remaining length in pixels
@N0330:  shift into to bits 8-13
@N0333:  initialize vector gen with the y-coord in ACC
@N0335:  shift from 0-15 axis to -8 to +7
@N0336:   +/- 1024 screen coords, multiply by 64 to get to bit 0
@N0337:  Draw a segment with x=ACC
@N0341:  =============================================================
@N0342:  save S; AC still = S
@N0343:  AC = S/2
@N0344:  AC = S/2 + 0.5
@N0345:  x0
@N0346:  --- Iteration 1 ---
@N0347:  BR = S / x  (AC = remainder, ignore)
@N0350:  AC = quotient from BR
@N0352:  AC = S/x + x
@N0353:  AC = (S/x + x) / 2
@N0355:  x1
@N0356:  --- Iteration 2 ---
@N0365:  x2
@N0366:  --- Iteration 3 ---
@N0375:  x3
@N0376:  --- Iteration 4 ---
@N0405:  x4
@N0406:  --- Iteration 5 ---
@N0415:  x5
@N0416:  --- Iteration 6: result stays in AC, no ts needed ---
@N0426:  saved input S
@N0427:  current Newton estimate
@N0430:  0.5 in fixed-point
